\par ATTACK ROLL
\par }{\fs20\cf0 An attack roll represents your attempt to strike your opponent on your turn in a round. When you make an attack roll, you roll a d20 and add your attack bonus. (Other modifiers may also apply to this roll.) If your re
sult equals or beats the target\rquote s Armor Class, you hit and deal damage.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Automatic Misses and Hits:}{\fs20\cf0  A natural 1 (the d20 comes up 1) on an attack roll is always a miss. A natural 20 (the d20 comes up 20) is always a hit. A natural 20 is also a threat\emdash a possible critical hit.
\par }{\cf0 
\par ATTACK BONUS
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Your attack bonus with a melee weapon is:
\par Base attack bonus + Strength modifier + size modifier
\par With a ranged weapon, your attack bonus is:
\par Base attack bonus + Dexterity modifier + size modifier + range penalty
